    "Therefore, it is important to control the shock or vibration frequency to avoid fruit damage (Norton et al. 1962).",
    "In order to minimize damage to the fruit tree caused by shock and to ensure that the fruit is smoothly removed from the canopy, both tree shapes were tested.",
    "The results showed that both shapes had a fruit picking rate of 90-95% with minimal damage to fruit and branches (Pellerin et al. 1978).",
    "In order to address the challenges associated with mechanical harvesting of sweet cherries and to reduce the damage caused to the fruit surface during dislodgement, an impact cherry picker was designed, characterized by the installation of an impact device on both sides of the branch.",
    "While the machine was able to achieve high efficiency (1480 kg/h) and high net picking rates, it was found that the use of two impact devices increased damage to the branches and affected fruiting rates the following year (Peterson et al. 2003)."
  ],
